    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>When Politics Is a Family Affair</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Alfred Gutmann letter comments on subheadline of July 30 front-page article on Gov George W Bush's planned address to Republican National Convention</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The subheadline on your July 30 front-page article ''Bush, in Address, Will Make Appeal Beyond the G.O.P.'' says it all: ''Fosters Harmony Theme; Uses 'Iron-Fist Rule' to Limit the Speakers and Present an Upbeat Message.'' Is that the way George W. Bush will govern the country if he is elected?</p>
        <p>ALFRED GUTMANN  Brookline, Mass., July 30, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The subheadline on your July 30 front-page article ''Bush, in Address, Will Make Appeal Beyond the G.O.P.'' says it all: ''Fosters Harmony Theme; Uses 'Iron-Fist Rule' to Limit the Speakers and Present an Upbeat Message.'' Is that the way George W. Bush will govern the country if he is elected?</p>
        <p>ALFRED GUTMANN  Brookline, Mass., July 30, 2000</p>
